    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2012-02-09</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2012-03-13T18:06:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>American Anti-Torture Act of 2012 - Amends the Detainee Treatment Act of 2005 to prohibit any person in the custody or control of the United States (under current law, the Department of Defense [DOD]) from being subject to any treatment or technique of interrogation not authorized by and listed in the U.S. Army Field Manual on Human Intelligence Collector Operations.</p> <p>Makes such prohibition inapplicable with respect to any person in the custody or control of the United States (under current law, DOD) pursuant to a U.S. criminal or immigration law.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
